<title type="html"><![CDATA[4/11(Sat.) Technicians is helping Taiwan mask production/11 Evidence-Based Benefits of Fish(Host: Cammy)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=381&amp;p=398#p398"><![CDATA[
4/11(Sat.) How team of technicians is helping Taiwan triple mask production/11 Evidence-Based Health Benefits of Eating Fish and The Healthiest Cooking Way(Host: Cammy)<br /><br />Session I:<br />How team of technicians is helping Taiwan triple mask production<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://chinapost.nownews.com/20200324-1096087">https://chinapost.nownews.com/20200324-1096087</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Extended watching video as follows:<br />RIYA SOKOL - &quot;Thank you, Coronavirus&quot; poem<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sgm9E_cmvWA&amp;feature=youtu.be">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sgm9E_c ... e=youtu.be</a><!-- m --><br />Taiwan expats thank gov’t efforts in virus containment<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://chinapost.nownews.com/20200330-1097946">https://chinapost.nownews.com/20200330-1097946</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion:<br />Q1 : This article mentioned “100 technicians whom recruited from companies across Taiwan, have spent the last six weeks assembling 92 surgical face mask production lines that will boost the country’s daily production capacity from 4 million to 13 million masks to prevent Covid-19 outbreak.” In your opinion, what benefits have 100 engineers contributed to Taiwanese society?<br />Q2 : In response to the outbreak of Covid-19 and the shortage of masks, what do you think the Taiwan government has done well or not?<br />Q3 : In this article, it is mentioned that the members of the national team share their stories of participating in the mask manufacturing. What stories are you touched   and why?<br />Q4 : What can we learn from Covid-19 outbreak until now?<br /><br />Session II:<br />11 Evidence-Based Health Benefits of Eating Fish and The Healthiest Cooking Way<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/11-health-benefits-of-fish">https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/11 ... ts-of-fish</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/healthiest-way-to-cook-fish">https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/he ... -cook-fish</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q1 : Referring to this article, what are the nutrients for fish? What kind of fish do you like best and share your cooking fish experience?<br />Q2 : What kinds of diseases can be reduced or prevented risk by eating fish? <br />Q3 : Eating fish one or two times per week is considered sufficient to reap its benefits. Do you think fish dish is easy to prepare? Why or why not?<br />Q4 : In this article mentioned, sous vide, microwaving, baking, steaming and poaching your fish are your best bets. Deep-frying fish is the least healthy cooking method. Which method will You choose? Why?<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 ~ 7:30 pm greetings &amp; free talk<br />7:30 ~ 8:15 pm guests introduced &amp; first session discussion<br />8:15 ~ 8:45 pm presentation, sharing the article &amp; other experiences<br />8:45 ~ 9:30 pm second session discussion<br /><br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven,<br />板橋民生路二段237 號,<br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30,<br />a minimum charge of Dante coffee for Royal English club attendant NT$80 (丹提低消80元)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.請帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Mon Apr 06, 2020 11:07 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
